  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AddAppointmentFormController
    Controls the AddAppointmentViewForm.fxml Pulls data from the form and runs it through logic checks before attempting to submit it to the database via AppointmentsQuery.insert()
    AddCustomerFormController
    Controls the AddCustomerForm.fxml Pulls data from the form and runs it through logic checks before attempting to submit it to the database via CustomersQuery.createCustomer()
    Appointments  
    AppointmentsQuery
    Contains various methods of querying the database for appointment information
    AppointmentsViewFormController
    Controls the AppointmentsViewForm.fxml Pulls the existing appointment information from the database, and allows the user to cycle through the appointments filtered by week, or month Also contains navigation to add, edit, or delete appointments
    Contacts  
    ContactsQuery
    Contains various methods of querying the database for contact information
    Countries  
    CountriesQuery
    Contains various methods of querying the database for country information
    Customers  
    CustomersQuery
    Contains various methods of querying the database for customer information
    CustomersViewFormController
    Controls the CustomersViewForm.fxml Pulls the existing customer information from the database Also contains navigation to add, edit, or delete customers
    EditAppointmentFormController
    Controls the EditAppointmentViewForm.fxml Populates the form with information passed in from the previous form on initialization On submission, pulls data from the form and runs it through logic checks before attempting to submit it to the database via AppointmentsQuery.update()
    EditCustomerFormController
    Controls the EditCustomerForm.fxml Populates the form with information passed in from the previous form on initialization On submission, pulls data from the form and runs it through logic checks before attempting to submit it to the database via Customer.updateCustomer()
    FirstLevelDivisions  
    FirstLevelDivisionsQuery
    Contains methods of querying the database for first-level divisions information
    HomePageFormController
    Controls the HomePageForm.fxml Runs a check on initialization for upcoming meetings for the user Contains navigation for bonus reports, appointments, and customers.
    JDBC
    Contains methods of opening and closing a connection to the database
    LogInFormController
    Controls the LogInForm.fxml On initialization, grabs information about the users' location/time zone, as well as the proper resource bundle to use for them.
    Main
    Javadoc files located in sjones_c195_assessment\javadoc
    reportAppointmentContactsFormController
    Controls the ReportAppointmentContactsForm.fxml Queries the database for appointments filtered by the customer specified in the drop-down on the form.
    ReportAppointmentTestingFormController
    Controls the ReportAppointmentTestingForm.fxml Queries the database for appointments filtered for Type containing the string of characters 'test', or, 'Test' and displays them
    reportAppointmentTotalsFormController
    Controls the ReportAppointmentTotalsForm.fxml Queries the database for the count of appointments grouped by type and then month and displays them
    Users  
    UsersQuery
    Contains methods of querying the database for user information, including the application sign in credential check functionality
